## Platform-Specific Realities

What works on YouTube fails on TikTok. What kills on Instagram dies on LinkedIn. Here's why.

## YouTube: The Long-Form King

**Algorithm priorities:**
- Average view duration (retention)
- Click-through rate (thumbnails/titles)
- Session time (keeping people on YouTube)
- Watch time (total minutes)

**Optimization strategy:**
- Strong hooks (first 30 seconds critical)
- Mid-roll payoffs (keep people watching)
- Clear thumbnails (high contrast, readable text)
- SEO-friendly titles (searchable keywords)
- End screens (keep people on your channel)

**Ideal length:** 8-15 minutes (sweet spot for ads + retention)

## TikTok: The Attention Battlefield

**Algorithm priorities:**
- Completion rate (did they watch to the end?)
- Rewatches (viral indicator)
- Engagement rate (likes, comments, shares)
- Watch time (in first few hours)

**Optimization strategy:**
- Hook in first 3 seconds (no intro)
- Vertical video (native format)
- Trending audio (algorithm boost)
- Text overlays (watch without sound)
- Loop-friendly endings (encourages rewatches)

**Ideal length:** 15-60 seconds (under 30 preferred)

## Instagram Reels: Visual-First

**Algorithm priorities:**
- Watch time (full views)
- Saves (strong signal)
- Shares (viral indicator)
- Completion rate

**Optimization strategy:**
- Visual hooks (eye-catching first frame)
- No watermarks (Instagram penalizes TikTok imports)
- Original audio or trending sounds
- Story-style pacing
- Save-worthy content (tutorials, tips)

**Ideal length:** 15-30 seconds

## LinkedIn: The Professional Play

**Algorithm priorities:**
- Dwell time (how long people watch)
- Engagement from connection network
- Professional relevance
- Comment quality (not just quantity)

**Optimization strategy:**
- Professional context (no fluff)
- Clear value proposition
- Subtitle-friendly (most watch muted)
- Thought leadership angle
- Native uploads (better reach than YouTube links)

**Ideal length:** 1-3 minutes

## Cross-Platform Strategy

**Don't:** Post the same content everywhere
**Do:** Adapt core content for each platform

**YouTube video → repurpose as:**
- TikTok: 3 short clips from key moments
- Instagram Reels: Best 30-second segment
- LinkedIn: Professional takeaway clip
- Twitter: Thread with key points + video

## Format Differences

**YouTube:**
- Landscape (16:9)
- High production value
- Longer storytelling
- Searchable/evergreen

**TikTok:**
- Vertical (9:16)
- Raw/authentic vibe
- Quick hits
- Trend-driven

**Instagram:**
- Vertical (9:16)
- Polished aesthetic
- Visual-first
- Save-worthy

**LinkedIn:**
- Square or horizontal
- Professional quality
- Subtitle essential
- Value-dense

## Timing and Frequency

**YouTube:** 1-2x per week, consistent schedule
**TikTok:** Daily (or multiple per day)
**Instagram:** 3-5 Reels per week
**LinkedIn:** 2-3x per week

## The Cross-Promotion Game

Use each platform to grow the others:

**YouTube → TikTok:** "Full version on YouTube" CTA
**TikTok → YouTube:** "Subscribe for deep dives"
**Instagram → Newsletter:** "Link in bio for free guide"
**LinkedIn → Website:** Professional portfolio/services

## The Bottom Line

One-size-fits-all doesn't work. Optimize for each platform's algorithm, format, and audience expectations.

The creators who win understand: it's not about being everywhere-it's about being optimized everywhere you show up.
    `
  }
]

export function getArticleBySlug(slug: string): Article | undefined {
  return articles.find(article => article.slug === slug)
}

export function getAllArticleSlugs(): string[] {
  return articles.map(article => article.slug)
}
